tip.text: Super place!! Get the Hells Bells pizza if you like a lil fire in your belly 😉
Beef cheek & steak sandwich - DELISH!
Their Belgian waffle - Awesomesauce! GF waffles available 😁
Possibly the best place for coffee in the CBD. Morning rush is pretty full on but you don't wait too long. Don't miss the bikes up on the wall.

Great coffee! Grab a coffee card & get your 8th free. I tried their watermelon & strawberry salad w/yoghurt - YUMMY. Visiting Adelaide for a week & these guys really helped with their recommendations.
Burger was a little cold but the flavours were great. I had the Gaucho & it was really juicy! Would've been better if bacon was crispy. The Castro has a nice kick to it, if you like a bit of spice...
Cosy little place with seating for about 15 people. Their black brew is FANTASTIC! Do say hi to Tiffany if she's around. Highly recommend this place! CLOSED - Monday's.
The west finally has GREAT coffee! Food is the usual cafe fare, all day brekkie, pizzas, pasta & baked rice. Cosy atmosphere. Average spend/person ~ $20 with coffee. Recommended!

formattedAddress: #B1-06/07, West Coast Plaza (154 West Coast Road)

tip.text: Good place if you want to indulge in people watching. Order a couple light snacks, a pint of relatively inexpensive beer (for the area) & enjoy their FREE wifi. I'll definitely be back here again.
Good cappuccino. Also tried the baileys molten cake with ice cream, which was divine! Haven't tried out the food... Maybe soon.

Cosy location with indoor/outdoor seating. Sit outdoors if you're heading there after sunset. Quite pricey w/ mains $20+ but everyone raves about the food. Coffee is average, salted caramel cake good.
Grab a table outdoors, order a pitcher of Pimms (great happy hour specials) & enjoy the beautiful sunset. Bangers & Mash and the Grilled Fish - GREAT!

Highly recommend ODP. Friendly staff are very helpful & know their menu well. We tried the Barramundi, Strawberry pancakes & beetroot risotto - all AMAZING! Apple crumble was delicious: $25-30 per pax
VERY popular for Sunday brunch. 15-20 mins of waiting is the norm. Great place to spend a lazy afternoon. I had the pork chop which was great, not too chewy & full of flavour. Try the daily specials.
Two words - CHILLI CRAB!! Amazing food, way better than the very commercial Jumbo IMO.
BQ & Mogambo - ROWDY & Fun! The Spiffy Dapper - Great cocktails. Popular Irish pub on the main road too. Can get decent discounts on food past 930pm with some places offering discounts up to 50%...
Get slayed at Sarnies' sister cafe. The latest slayer machine pulls your shots & for the most part, they are good. Pumpkin salad is VERY filling and the panini delicious BUT very messy.
Great folks, great coffee. I go here A LOT!! Haven't tried the food yet, but can vouch for their cappuccino & flat white - FANTASTIC. Opening hours are best as it's always crowded. CLOSED - Wednesday
The ultimate croissant is DELICIOUS! Ham, bacon, egg, cheese, heaven 😁 Bangers & mash tasty too!
Hole in the wall cafe. Hard to find if you're not familiar with the area. Coffee is good, didn't try the food. Forget about finding a place to sit on weekends.
#ProTip - Get an Iced Grande 1 Pump Mocha Chai. It is DA BOMB!
Great quiche and coffee. Gotta get there early though as almost nothing ever lasts past 1pm.

formattedAddress: Ground Floor, JW Marriott (Senapati Bapat Road)

tip.text: Amazing ice-cream. Love their Nutella flavour!! Can go through a tub in one sitting 😁

formattedAddress: #01-02, Holland Village Shopping Centre (3 Lor Liput)

tip.text: Their Mont Blanc is AMAZING!

formattedAddress: #01-11, The Pier @ Robertson (80 Mohamed Sultan Rd.)

tip.text: Great coffee, great staff but is quite noisy no matter what time of day you're there. If the loud talking hipsters don't get you, the music will. Tasty sandwiches & hot chocolate is DA BOMB. Do try!
Get EVERYTHING! Okay, if I had to choose, I'd go for the G-Spot & the pastry in the picture (can't remember what it's called). Coffee is quite good too. Pricey but oh-so-good :)
They use Yahava beans, which I hadn't tried. Coffee was good. Didn't order anything to eat but did get apple pie take-away for friends who said it was amazing! They also do beers & cider :) #Friendly
Great coffee but make sure to ask for the Nylon coffee blend (I'm not a fan of common man coffee). Although the coffee was great, I ordered a Moroccan omelette & was served 2 eggs sunny side up!!
Tucked away in the housing estate at Telok Blangah, TMT's a cute cafe. Everything is served with a marshmallow, hence the name. Tried out their waffles & coffee, both were okay. Enjoy their swing!
Book pre-10am & on weekdays for better(read cheaper) rates! Turf is in decent knick and the location is convenient. Bus stop 2 mins away & Farrer Park MRT 5 min walk.
Surprisingly good coffee. I'm not a fan of coffee chains but have them a try and their Cappucino was great! Alternate location at Chijmes.
Newly opened... There's some links that need worked out. Hopefully they will. Rolled ham & cheese sandwich is deep fried comfort food (pretty good too).

tip.text: Have their hot turkey bagel. It's yummy! Also, affagato with chocolate chip cookie crumbs is delish :D
Beautiful view! Nice Shiraz.

tip.text: Head there in the morning & watch the mountains get enveloped by clouds!!
FANTASTIC Hot Chocolate!! Even the Trunkey Chorizo & Pepperoni Pizza was delicious.

formattedAddress: Queen Elizabeth Dr. (btwn Notts Ave. & Ramsgate Ave.)

tip.text: Amazing food. Escargot is delicious. Go there early or you won't get to have their orgasmic tarts!!

formattedAddress: #03-96, The Central (6 Eu Tong Sen St)

tip.text: Decent food, friendly staff! Definitely worth a try.
Chill place w/ lotta backpackers & a nice collection of craft beers.

venue.name: Nam Seng Noodles & Fried Rice 南生麵家

tip.text: Great salads!! Gets really crowded around 1 but the guys are really efficient. Was in & out in 10 mins. Hail Caesar with bacon - yummy. Will definitely go back to try the other salads.
Nice coffee & surprising cheap beer if you're in the mood for a cold one post work. Tiger, Corona & Heineken bottles are $6++. Nice place to go if you feel like taking a break on a busy day.

Cosy brunch joint. Beetroot risotto with goat cheese was delicious & so was the barramundi, cooked pedfect with a crispy skin! Apple crumble with creme anglaise was delicious. Last order@1445 (pricey)

Went here for a Latte after lunch. Supposed to be top 10 in Singapore, but I wouldn't agree with that. Great place for brunch. Go early cuz it gets VERY busy. Will definitely go back for food sometime
Great place to people watch & enjoy a cold one. Has Guinness on tap & if you're in the service industry, $10 pints on Thursdays & cocktails are 1 for 1 all day, everyday.

formattedAddress: G/F Singapore Marriott Hotel, 320 Orchard Rd. (at Scotts Rd.)
location.address: G/F Singapore Marriott Hotel, 320 Orchard Rd.

tip.text: Great chocolates & pastries. I've tried the Vanilla Flan & Mont Blanc. Both were fantastic! Free coffee with your pastry from 2-6pm.

formattedAddress: #01-11, The Pier @ Robertson (80 Mohamed Sultan Rd.)

tip.text: Great place for Sunday brunch, even though it gets quite busy. Service can take up to 20-25 mins during peak hours & there's a 75min limit for keeping a table (unlikely they enforce this though).
Reasonably priced sandwiches. Chocolate chip cookie was average.

The XIPA & Punk IPA (pictured) are great. The Oatmeal Stout is pretty good too.
